modules.description: Provides a single test function that evaluates a predefined test case. Operates on a custom test type containing test specifications and expected outcomes. Used to validate specific system behaviors during automated verification processes.

Encodes and decodes integers into short, unique strings using a custom alphabet and salt. Processes lists of integers and returns corresponding hash strings, and vice versa. Useful for generating compact, URL-safe identifiers from database IDs.

Handles validation of system behaviors through predefined test cases, using a custom test type to encapsulate specifications and expected results. Supports automated verification by executing and evaluating test scenarios. Allows developers to check correctness of hash generation and parsing against known inputs and outputs. Enables precise debugging by isolating and testing specific edge cases.
